gape is not trumped by justice or other goods. Rather, agape precedes justice: without the work of love, society would not produce persons capable of merit, demerit, and contract, the elements of most modern conceptions of justice. Jackson then considers the implications of his ideas for several questions: the nature of God, the relation between Christian love and political violence, the place of forgiveness, and the morality of abortion. Arguing that agapic love is to be construed as a gift of grace as well as a divine commandment, Jackson concludes that love is the "eternal life" that makes temporal existence possible and thus the "first" Christian virtue. Though foremost a contribution to Christian ethics, Jackson's arguments and the issues he takes up will find a broader readership.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh  aEnlightenment.  aGood Samaritan.  aHindus.  aJudaism.  aabortion.  aagape: as a metavalue.  aaltruism.  aanger.  aanorexia.  aanti-essentialism.  aautonomy, the autonomous.  abenevolence, the benevolent.  abestowal (of worth).  abody.  acertainty, certitude.  acompassion.  acooperation.  acovenant, the covenantal.  acrucifixion.  adespair.  adignity.  adread, the dreadful.  aempathy.  aeternity, the eternal.  aethic of manageability.  aevolution.  afallibility, fallibilism.  afreedom, the free.  agender, gender relations.  ahumility.  aimmortality.  ainfanticide.  aintolerance.  ainvulnerability.  aliberty.  aliberum arbitrium.  amartyrdom.  amisanthropy.  amonotheism.  amortality.  amutuality.  anonresistance.  aobedience.  apacifism.  apunishment.  areconciliation.  areverence.  asalvation.  asuffering.  atenderness.  aterrorism, terrorists.08iTitle is part of eBook p